Structural functionalism, or simply functionalism, is a framework for building theory that sees society as a complex system whose parts work together to promote solidarity and stability. Two theorists, Herbert Spencer and Robert Merton, were major contributors to this perspective.he structural-functional approach is a perspective in sociology that sees society as a complex system whose parts work together to promote solidarity and stability.
